; skill-vitality.form
;
; A skill is a teachable cell with a grammar, a runnable recipe, a proof row,
; supported carrier/metal rows, vitality receipts, auto-research questions, and
; an earned upgrade gate.
;
; The loop:
;
;   skill cell
;     -> carrier execution receipt
;     -> vitality row
;     -> focus route
;     -> auto-research candidate
;     -> challenger execution receipt
;     -> promote only when measured vitality improves
;
; Carriers are not authority. A Mac CPU, Android arm64 binary, Metal GPU lane,
; MLX buffer, remote LLM, API route, or file cache can execute a skill, but each
; must return measured receipts. The source truth is the skill row plus proof.
;
; Vitality is not a single score. The row keeps accuracy, trust, sovereignty,
; coverage, freshness, energy, latency, memory, proof count, sample count, and
; residual questions separate so the focus stays honest: teach trust, restore
; sovereignty, learn samples, refresh sources, answer residuals, compress or
; route, or serve and watch.
;
; Auto-research does not promote by imagination. It may propose a challenger
; when evidence, residual questions, expected lift, and risk are visible. The
; challenger earns the body only when its receipts show better vitality and a
; ready cheaper carrier.
;
; Carrier:
;   form/form-stdlib/skill-vitality.fk
;
; Proof:
;   form/form-stdlib/tests/skill-vitality-band.fk -> 65535 four-way
;
; Kin:
;   code-tool-learning.form
;   tool-embodiment.form
;   model-vitality.form
;   autoresearch-runtime.form
;   real-mesh-training-carrier.form
